132nd MAINE LEGISLATURE
FIRST REGULAR SESSION-2025
Legislative Document No. 920
H.P. 585 House of Representatives, March 11, 2025
Resolve, to Review Efficiencies in the Licensing of Solid Waste
Disposal Facilities by the Department of Environmental Protection
Received by the Clerk of the House on March 5, 2025. Referred to the Committee on
Environment and Natural Resources pursuant to Joint Rule 308.2 and ordered printed pursuant
to Joint Rule 401.
ROBERT B. HUNT
Clerk
Presented by Representative CAMPBELL of Orrington.
Cosponsored by Senator MARTIN of Oxford and
Representatives: BRIDGEO of Augusta, SCHMERSAL-BURGESS of Mexico, SOBOLESKI
of Phillips, THORNE of Carmel, WOODSOME of Waterboro.
Printed on recycled paper

1 Sec. 1. Department of Environmental Protection to review efficiency of
2 solid waste disposal facility licensing. Resolved: That the Department of
3 Environmental Protection shall review the requirements in statute, department rules and
4 department policies that apply to the licensing of solid waste disposal facilities. The
5 purpose of the review is to identify efficiencies and inefficiencies in the license review
6 process. The review must include a general review of the license review process and a
7 targeted review of the license review process related to the Penobscot Energy Recovery
8 Company's waste-to-energy facility in the Town of Orrington. The review must also
9 include, but is not limited to, a review of impediments to the efficient review of license
10 applications, renewals and modifications; processing timelines and whether deadlines are
11 typically met and, if not, causes for the delays; ways to improve staffing to eliminate
12 inefficiencies; and methods to improve the licensing process. The department shall
13 establish a stakeholder group to advise the department on matters relating to the review.
14 By December 3, 2025, the department shall submit a report relating to the review, including
15 recommendations and any suggested legislation, to the Joint Standing Committee on
16 Environment and Natural Resources. The joint standing committee may report out a bill
17 relating to the report to the Second Regular Session of the 132nd Legislature.
18 SUMMARY
1199 This resolve directs the Department of Environmental Protection to review the
2200 requirements in statute, department rules and department policies that apply to the licensing
2211 of solid waste disposal facilities. The purpose of the review is to identify efficiencies and
2222 inefficiencies in the license review process. The review must include a general review of
2233 the license review process and a targeted review of the license review process related to the
2244 Penobscot Energy Recovery Company's waste-to-energy facility in the Town of Orrington.
